     <div class="textIndent"> <div class="rhnLinkText">The British Isles has seven officially recognised minority languages under the European Charter for Regional or Minority languages. They are: <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/voices/multilingual/welsh.shtml">Welsh</a>, <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/voices/multilingual/scots_gaelic.shtml">Scottish Gaelic</a>, <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/voices/multilingual/irish.shtml">Irish Gaelic</a>, <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/voices/multilingual/cornish.shtml">Cornish</a>, <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/voices/multilingual/scots.shtml">Lowland Scots</a>, <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/voices/multilingual/ulster-scots.shtml">Ulster Scots</a> and <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/voices/multilingual/bsl_today.shtml">British Sign Language</a>.</div> </div>  
